分析每一個欄位中Adaptivity Level分布比例(圓餅圖)¶

In [3]:
# 根據特定欄位繪製各項種類的"Adaptivity Level"分布比例圓餅圖
def GetPie( target="Gender" ):
    # 設定畫布相關設定
    figSize = 4
    wordSize = 12
    rowSize = df.nunique( axis=0 )[ target ] // 3 # 幾列
    if ( rowSize <= 1 ) :
        rowSize = 1
    else : # 超過三個
        figSize = rowSize * 2 # 畫面大小
        wordSize = rowSize * 6
    
    plt.figure( figsize=( figSize * 4 ,figSize * rowSize ) ) 

    # 繪製各種類圓餅圖
    i = 1
    for item in df[ target ].unique() :
        plt.subplot( rowSize, 3, i ) # 顯示於畫布的位置
        plt.title( item, {'fontsize': wordSize + 2 } )
        df_plot = df[ df[ target ]==item ]["Adaptivity Level"].value_counts().sort_index(ascending=True) # 每一種level數量
        labels = sorted( df[ df[ target ]==item ]["Adaptivity Level"].unique() ) # 有哪幾個level名稱
        plt.pie( df_plot, labels=labels, autopct = "%1.1f%%", textprops = {"fontsize" : wordSize }, )
        i += 1

    plt.show()

def AnalyzeTwoCondition( firstColumn, secondColumn ) :
    display( df.groupby([ firstColumn, secondColumn ]).agg([ "mean", "min", "max", "std", "count" ]) )
    df.groupby([ firstColumn, secondColumn ]).mean().plot( kind="line", figsize=( 15, 5 ) )

#欄位數值轉換
df_level = pd.DataFrame()
df_level["Age"] = df["Age"].map({ "1-5":1, "6-10":2, "11-15":3, "16-20":4, "21-25":5, "26-30":6 })
df_level["Education Level"] = df["Education Level"].map({ "School":1, "College":3.5, "University":6 })
df_level["Load-shedding"] = df["Load-shedding"].map({ "Low":1, "High":6 })
df_level["Network Type"] = df["Network Type"].map({ "2G":1, "3G":3.5, "4G":6 })
df_level["Class Duration"] = df["Class Duration"].map({ "0":1, "1-3":3.5, "3-6":6 })
df_level["Adaptivity Level"] = df["Adaptivity Level"].map({ "Low":1, "Moderate":3.5, "High":6 })

# 畫折線圖
fig, ax = plt.subplots()
for target in df_level :
    # 對每種欄位(column)的每項level做Adaptivity Level平均
    if ( target == "Adaptivity Level" ) :
        continue
    else :
        df_temp_level = df_level[[ "Adaptivity Level", target ]].groupby( [ target ] ).mean() # 將不同level作為index，對於Adaptivity Level做平均
        df_temp_level = df_temp_level.rename( columns={ "Adaptivity Level": target } ) # 把重新命名column位，以便折線圖上顯示
        ax = df_temp_level.plot( kind="line", xlabel="level", ylabel="Adaptivity Level", ax=ax, figsize=( 15, 5 ) )

adapttability_df = pd.read_csv("students_adaptability_level_online_education.csv")
# All feature in this dataset are categorical data.

# Some feature are have only two category, so use one hot encoding to change the category to value.
# Gender、Institution Type、IT Student、Location、Load-shedding、Internet Type、Self Lms
adapttability_df["Gender"].replace("Boy",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Gender"].replace("Girl",  2, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Institution Type"].replace("Non Government",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Institution Type"].replace("Government",  2, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["IT Student"].replace("No",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["IT Student"].replace("Yes",  2, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Location"].replace("No",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Location"].replace("Yes",  2, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Load-shedding"].replace("Low",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Load-shedding"].replace("High",  2, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Internet Type"].replace("Wifi",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Internet Type"].replace("Mobile Data",  2, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Self Lms"].replace("No",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Self Lms"].replace("Yes",  2, inplace = True)

# Some feature are represent different degree, so use label encoding to change the category to value.
# Age、Education Level、Financial Condition、Network Type、Class Duration、Adaptivity Level
adapttability_df["Age"].replace("1-5", 1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Age"].replace("6-10",  2, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Age"].replace("11-15",  3, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Age"].replace("16-20", 4, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Age"].replace("21-25",  5, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Age"].replace("26-30",  6, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Education Level"].replace("School",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Education Level"].replace("University",  2, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Education Level"].replace("College",  3, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Financial Condition"].replace("Poor",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Financial Condition"].replace("Mid",  2, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Financial Condition"].replace("Rich",  3, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Network Type"].replace("2G",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Network Type"].replace("3G",  2, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Network Type"].replace("4G",  3, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Class Duration"].replace("0",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Class Duration"].replace("1-3",  2, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Class Duration"].replace("3-6",  3, inplace = True)

adapttability_df["Adaptivity Level"].replace("Low",  1, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Adaptivity Level"].replace("Moderate",  2, inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Adaptivity Level"].replace("High",  3, inplace = True)


# Some feature is didn't represent different degree, and we guess that some information can be extracted on the frequency.
# So use frequency encoding to change the category to value.
# Device
adapttability_df["Device"].replace("Tab",  adapttability_df["Device"].where(adapttability_df["Device"] == 'Tab').count(), inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Device"].replace("Mobile",  adapttability_df["Device"].where(adapttability_df["Device"] == 'Mobile').count(), inplace = True)
adapttability_df["Device"].replace("Computer",  adapttability_df["Device"].where(adapttability_df["Device"] == 'Computer').count(), inplace = True)

In [43]:
import seaborn as sns

The scatter plot is a common way to show how the data distributed. the following is try to use scatter plot to show where exist the data.¶

But the scatter plot can't show many data in one dot. The dot has only one data looks same as the dot has 10 or more data. So the scatter plot can't show the density of this dataset. And because we use encoding to handle category data. So it can exist data in few dot, not everywhere.So a little different data can fill up all possible dot and we can't see more information in scatter plot.¶

Conclusion:scatter plot is not suitable to this dataset¶¶

But for one pair of data: Age and Education Level, their correlation is 0.595284. High and positive correlation. We can see the correlation trend on scatter plot. (the second row and third column on the first plot)
